start_time = time.time()
with open("wiki_100k.txt") as lines:
    metadata = lines.readline()
    metadata = metadata.rstrip("\n").rstrip(" ").split(" ")
    number_of_examples = int(metadata[0])
    number_of_dimensions = int(metadata[1])
    wikipedia_vectors = np.zeros(shape=(number_of_examples,number_of_dimensions), dtype=np.float32)
    for line_number, line in enumerate(lines):
        vector_data = np.asarray(line.rstrip("\n").split(" ")[1:number_of_dimensions+1], dtype=np.float32)
        wikipedia_vectors[line_number,:] = vector_data
end_time = time.time()

print("Loaded vectors representing Wikipedia articles in {} seconds".format(end_time - start_time))
        
print(wikipedia_vectors.shape)
print(wikipedia_vectors[0][:])

reduced_dimensions = 3

n_neighbors = 100 # this parameter is critical to the global vs. local structure in UMAP
                  # e.g. 5 -> very local, 100 -> smooth structures across batches of 100

start_time = time.time()
mapper = umap.UMAP(n_components=reduced_dimensions, n_neighbors=n_neighbors)
embeddings = mapper.fit_transform(sample_of_wikipedia_vectors)
end_time = time.time()
print("UMAP dimensionality reduction on {} samples with {} neighbors from {}D to {}D in {} seconds".format(sample_size, n_neighbors, number_of_dimensions, reduced_dimensions, end_time - start_time))

import hdbscan

clustering_sample_size = sample_size
target_clusters = 500
min_cluster_size = int(clustering_sample_size / (4*target_clusters)) # in practice, setting a min cluster size at 1/4 of target cluster size delivers order of magnitude closeness
start_time = time.time()
cluster_labels = hdbscan.HDBSCAN(min_cluster_size=min_cluster_size, min_samples=2).fit_predict(embeddings)

# compute mean in x,y,z dimensions and subtract from it ("zero mean")
average_x = np.average(embeddings[:,0])
average_y = np.average(embeddings[:,1])
if reduced_dimensions == 3:
    average_z = np.average(embeddings[:,2])

json_dict["y"] = (embeddings[:,1] - average_y).tolist()
if reduced_dimensions == 3:

json_dict["cluster_ids"] = cluster_labels.tolist()
